      "writtenOn": "2020-01-14T21:19:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So changing this from config to colorType is valid today. Having an RGBA/BGRA_8888_PixelConfig means that we had a colorType of GrColorType::kRGBA/BGRA_8888 and a backendFormat that is the typical RGBA/BGRA_8888 unorm format for the given API. Today the only formats that back an RGBA_8888 colorType are these basic formats. So by just checking the colorType we know we have a valid backendFormat as well and don\u0027t need to check that they are the APIs RGBA/BGRA_8888 format.\n\nIf however in the future we allow the GrColorType::kRGBA/BGRA_8888 to be backed by weirder formats that can\u0027t do this canvas2DFastPath then we\u0027d need a way to check the formats are safe as well as the colorType. I could add to caps a silly query like \"bool isFormatRGBAorBGRA888Unorm(GrBackendFormat)\", but I feel like that is not needed now. Thoughts?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 195,
        "startChar": 29,
        "endLine": 196,
        "endChar": 67
      },
